</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drill a small hole through the cap/cork as this area will receive the cotton wick. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2d/Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-13Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-13Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2d/Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-13Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-13Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Bring the wick back through the plywood circle and then cap. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a5\/Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/a\/a5\/Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Tie wick against the cap and leave one end of the wick approximately 8 inches (20.3 cm) long. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/cc\/Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/cc\/Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-Candelabras-from-Old-Bottles-Step-16Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Pass the long end of the wick through the pipe into the bottle’s neck and then outside the top.
